Britannia Industries processes raw materials like wheat flour, water, fats, sugar, and leavening agents into biscuits through a six step manufacturing process. The key steps are: (1) making dough by mixing ingredients, (2) fermenting the dough, (3) shaping the dough into biscuits using machines like laminators and rotary cutters, (4) baking the raw biscuits, (5) testing and cooling the biscuits, and (6) packaging and distributing the biscuits.
